1
00:00:21,633 --> 00:00:25,800
The whole university
is excited about our return.

2
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:26,733
Good job, girls!

3
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:27,800
Good job!

4
00:00:27,867 --> 00:00:29,500
Especially you, Eden.

5
00:00:29,567 --> 00:00:32,733
You did great in Davao!

6
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,700
Thank you.

7
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:37,400
You made us all proud!

8
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:39,667
You're the best!

9
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:41,433
You have a great chance

10
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:46,500
to be part of the Philippine
swimming team next season!

11
00:00:46,567 --> 00:00:48,300
I'm so jealous!

12
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:52,667
Aren't you happy, Eden?

13
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:55,100
I'm happy, Coach.

14
00:00:55,167 --> 00:01:01,633
I just feel bad
that my mom didn't see me win.

15
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:08,400
How is the appeal going?

16
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:13,700
We're still waiting
for the result.

17
00:01:13,767 --> 00:01:16,433
Sometimes...

18
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:19,533
I feel like I'm losing hope.

19
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:22,867
My mom's been in prison
for 8 years now.

20
00:01:22,933 --> 00:01:25,133
We've been waiting for 8 years.

21
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:30,667
I don't know if
she'll ever get out of prison.

22
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:35,133
Or when she'd get out.

23
00:01:36,867 --> 00:01:39,200
Don't lose hope, Eden.

24
00:01:39,267 --> 00:01:42,900
God listens to all our prayers.

25
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:48,000
You have to stay strong for now.

26
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:53,767
All your dreams will come true
for you and your mom.

27
00:01:54,633 --> 00:01:56,200
Smile.

28
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:57,233
Thank you, Coach.

29
00:02:01,867 --> 00:02:03,533
Get some rest.

30
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,533
You, too.

31
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:05,867
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

32
00:02:05,933 --> 00:02:07,300
This is your Captain speaking.

33
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:09,933
I would like to welcome
you all aboard this flight

34
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,300
going to Manila.

35
00:02:11,367 --> 00:02:15,167
Our flight time is approximately
one hour and fifteen minutes.

36
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:17,533
Here, Mom. Take your meds.

37
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,800
So your wounds will heal.

38
00:02:19,867 --> 00:02:20,567
Thank you, Dear.

39
00:02:21,733 --> 00:02:22,800
For your safety,

40
00:02:22,867 --> 00:02:25,267
please keep your seatbelts
securely fastened

41
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,700
whenever you are seated.

42
00:02:26,767 --> 00:02:29,433
And in the meantime,
please sit back and relax.

43
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:30,400
Enjoy the flight.
Thank you.

44
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:44,867
Raichu, I'll just use
the restroom.

45
00:02:44,933 --> 00:02:45,833
Okay.

46
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:07,867
Eden?

47
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:09,267
Raichu, where's Yenyen?

48
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,200
I don't know!
Yen!

49
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:11,700
Mayday!

50
00:03:11,767 --> 00:03:13,433
Flight 1884.

51
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:14,500
We have an engine problem.

52
00:03:14,567 --> 00:03:16,567
Let's pray!

53
00:03:16,633 --> 00:03:17,167
Lord, Lord!

54
00:03:17,233 --> 00:03:19,167
Please help us, Lord!

55
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:21,700
Squawk 7700.

56
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,367
Everyone, basic position!

57
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:24,933
Put your hands here...

58
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,567
Heads down. Stay down!

59
00:03:26,633 --> 00:03:28,333
Your life vest is
under the seat!

60
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,467
Heads down! Stay down!

61
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:36,233
Mayday!

62
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,433
Preparing for an emergency
landing.

63
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,233
Preparing for an emergency
landing.

64
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:11,733
Squawk 7700.

65
00:04:27,733 --> 00:04:29,900
Let's see...

66
00:04:29,967 --> 00:04:31,733
if this will look good on you.

67
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,100
Oh, dear!

68
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:37,633
It looks great on you, Yenyen!

69
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,333
Come on, Mom.

70
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,167
Why do you keep
calling me Yenyen?

71
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:42,633
Why not?

72
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:46,067
You'll stay as my baby
even when you're older.

73
00:04:46,133 --> 00:04:47,167
Mom!

74
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:50,167
Yes!

75
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:52,367
But Mom,

76
00:04:52,433 --> 00:04:53,633
this is too nice.

77
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:54,800
Don't you like it?

78
00:04:54,867 --> 00:04:56,067
Of course, I like it.

79
00:04:56,133 --> 00:04:57,667
But...

80
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:59,300
this looks expensive.

81
00:04:59,367 --> 00:05:00,733
It really is expensive.

82
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,500
What?
Yes.

83
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:05,567
But you're more precious!

84
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:07,033
Mom!

85
00:05:09,367 --> 00:05:13,767
I was your age when your
grandmother gave this to me.

86
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:16,500
She inherited it
from my grandmother.

87
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:20,400
And now you're the rightful
owner of this necklace.

88
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:23,367
Look, I have them engrave
your name on it.

89
00:05:23,433 --> 00:05:25,767
Because it's all yours.

90
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:29,300
And no one else can have it.

91
00:05:29,367 --> 00:05:30,533
Take care of it.

92
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:33,633
That's your advance
birthday gift.

93
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:34,167
Okay.

94
00:05:34,267 --> 00:05:36,133
Thank you, Mom.

95
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,633
I will wear this all the time.

96
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:40,233
To remind me of you.

97
00:05:41,867 --> 00:05:45,967
Especially now
that you're leaving soon.

98
00:05:46,033 --> 00:05:47,767
Are you really going to leave?

99
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,400
Yes.

100
00:05:49,467 --> 00:05:51,867
We already talked
about this, right?

101
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:57,700
Don't worry,
I'll be here on my day off.

102
00:05:57,767 --> 00:06:01,933
But Mom, you'll only
be home once a week.

103
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:05,167
It feels like
you're going abroad.

104
00:06:05,233 --> 00:06:07,933
But I have to do it.

105
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:11,333
I have to work for your college.

106
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:16,633
Do you think our life would be
different if Dad was here?

107
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:20,167
Eden, I love your dad.

108
00:06:20,233 --> 00:06:23,167
But he left us
since you were little.

109
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:29,667
It hurts and is hard to accept,
but I'll stay strong for you.

110
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:32,467
To make all your
dreams come true.

111
00:06:32,533 --> 00:06:35,500
And all my dreams for you.

112
00:06:35,567 --> 00:06:37,733
Thank you, Mom.

113
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:43,233
I'm just sad you have
to be away just to make money.

114
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:45,667
We have to make
a little sacrifice.

115
00:06:45,733 --> 00:06:46,700
Right?

116
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:49,067
We'll get through this.

117
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,867
Can you stop
pestering me, Amanda?

118
00:06:58,933 --> 00:07:02,600
I don't care how long you've
been asking for a day off.

119
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:05,467
I already told you that you
can't have a day off today.

120
00:07:05,533 --> 00:07:07,500
You have to watch Angelo.

121
00:07:07,567 --> 00:07:08,933
Mom, I'm okay.

122
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,900
Let her have a day off.

123
00:07:10,967 --> 00:07:15,567
Angelo, she doesn't have
a say on this.

124
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:17,433
The answer is no.

125
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:21,167
Anyway, I have to go.

126
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:24,033
I'm gonna go see your
dad and your brother

127
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:26,033
before they leave
for the airport.

128
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,233
Don't you want to come with me?

129
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:30,467
I'll just call dad
to say goodbye.

130
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:31,933
I'll just wait for you here.

131
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:36,300
Okay, if that's what you want.

132
00:07:36,367 --> 00:07:38,100
Keep an eye on him, okay?

133
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,100
I'll go ahead.

134
00:07:41,167 --> 00:07:42,333
Take care.

135
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,033
Bye.
Bye.

136
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:04,333
Sorry, Eden.

137
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,267
You have to see that.

138
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:08,100
It's okay, Mom.

139
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:10,500
We can't do anything about it.

140
00:08:10,567 --> 00:08:13,567
Let's just celebrate
on Saturday, okay?

141
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:14,733
But...

142
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:18,733
can I stay here
for a little while?

143
00:08:21,433 --> 00:08:27,267
Angelo, can she stay here
for a little bit?

144
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,133
She'll go home later.

145
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,300
It's fine with me.

146
00:08:30,367 --> 00:08:32,433
Just don't let my mom see her.

147
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,233
You know how she is.

148
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:35,333
Thank you.

149
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,200
Okay.

150
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:40,467
Happy birthday, Yenyen!

151
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:45,267
Come on, let's eat
the noodles together.

152
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,300
You have to go home now.

153
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:54,567
I don't want you
to be outside late at night.

154
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:57,900
But Mom, I still want
to spend time with you.

155
00:08:57,967 --> 00:09:00,067
It's my birthday anyway.

156
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:02,267
Let me spend time
with you as a gift.

157
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:04,567
You're so sweet.

158
00:09:04,633 --> 00:09:07,733
I promise that
I will do everything

159
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:11,000
to give you a comfortable life.

160
00:09:11,067 --> 00:09:16,833
I will work hard for us
to have a better life.

161
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:20,200
So you won't have
to work like this.

162
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:23,633
Just work hard for your future.

163
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:27,833
So you won't become
a maid like us.

164
00:09:34,267 --> 00:09:35,900
I'm glad you're here.

165
00:09:35,967 --> 00:09:38,033
I need to get something
in the quarters.

166
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:40,233
I just need to get my things.

167
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:42,533
I thought you got
all your stuff already.

168
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,067
Why do you need
to come back here?

169
00:09:44,133 --> 00:09:46,533
And you can't go inside
because Ma'am Rina is not home.

170
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,333
Come on, Amanda.

171
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,167
I won't take long.

172
00:09:49,233 --> 00:09:50,433
It's not like I'm a stranger.

173
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,733
You can't come in here.

174
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,367
Amanda, I've worked
here longer than you.

175
00:09:55,433 --> 00:09:56,367
But you don't work here anymore.

176
00:09:56,433 --> 00:09:58,933
Don't you trust me?

177
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,233
No.

178
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:01,767
You're not allowed to come in.

179
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,033
Who is this?

180
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,233
My daughter.

181
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,900
Wow.

182
00:10:13,967 --> 00:10:16,133
Your grumpy boss
let you bring her here?

183
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:22,000
Fine, I'll go with you
to the quarters.

184
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:25,100
Take all your stuff
and go. Okay?

185
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:26,467
Okay.

186
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:27,333
Come on.

187
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:34,667
Hurry up, okay?

188
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:35,933
Just get your things and go.

189
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,067
I have a lot to do.

190
00:10:57,033 --> 00:10:58,267
Why did you take that?

191
00:10:58,333 --> 00:10:59,500
Be quiet! Or I'll hurt you!

192
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:00,400
Mom!

193
00:11:00,467 --> 00:11:01,633
- Mom, he took something!
- Be quiet!

194
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,300
What did you take?

195
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:04,867
- Stay out of it!
- Mom!

196
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,267
Mom!

197
00:11:08,367 --> 00:11:09,333
Mom!

198
00:11:16,367 --> 00:11:17,733
Mom, are you okay?

199
00:11:24,467 --> 00:11:25,200
Raul!
No!

200
00:11:35,733 --> 00:11:37,000
Angelo!

201
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,233
Angelo!

202
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,967
Angelo!

203
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:53,267
You're a monster, Raul!

204
00:11:55,167 --> 00:11:56,200
Angelo!

205
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,133
You need to come with us
to the police station

206
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,533
to get your statement.

207
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:10,567
Can I bring
my daughter home first?

208
00:12:10,633 --> 00:12:11,233
No, Ma'am.

209
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:12,967
You need to come with us.

210
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:13,733
Go home?

211
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:14,833
Who's going home?

212
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:16,433
You're not going anywhere!

213
00:12:18,667 --> 00:12:20,233
Bring her to the
police station!

214
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:21,767
Take her!

215
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:23,400
You are Raul's accomplice!

216
00:12:23,467 --> 00:12:24,933
You planned this together!

217
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,833
- You killed my son!
- I have nothing to do with it!

218
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,400
Take her to the station!

219
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:30,100
She's a criminal!

220
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:31,400
Murderer!

221
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:34,200
- You killed my son!
- I didn't do anything wrong!

222
00:12:34,267 --> 00:12:35,300
Let go of me!

223
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:37,433
- Please, calm down.
- Let go of me!

224
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,600
- Put her in jail!
- I didn't do anything wrong.

225
00:12:39,667 --> 00:12:40,900
Put her in jail!

226
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:43,867
She will rot in there!

227
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:46,700
You killed my son!

228
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:49,033
You did this with Raul!

229
00:12:51,867 --> 00:12:55,933
Whereof, the court finds
the accused, Amanda Sta. Maria,

230
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:59,800
guilty beyond reasonable doubt
as accomplice to the crime

231
00:12:59,867 --> 00:13:01,767
of robbery with homicide

232
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:05,933
as defined and penalized under
the revised penal code.

233
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,133
So ordered.

234
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:09,667
Why did this happen?

235
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:11,267
My mom didn't do anything wrong!

236
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:14,300
Please don't take her
from me, I'm begging you.

237
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:15,300
She didn't do anything.
Eden, we can't do
anything about it now.

238
00:13:16,333 --> 00:13:17,867
Come on, Eden.

239
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:18,767
Stop.

240
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:21,067
You didn't do
anything wrong, Mom!

241
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:23,633
Can I say goodbye to her
before you take me away?

242
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:24,867
Mom!

243
00:13:24,933 --> 00:13:26,833
- I can't let this happen.
- I love you so much, Eden.

244
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,667
Mom!

245
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:33,600
Dindi, take care of my daughter.

246
00:13:35,033 --> 00:13:37,533
Don't take my mom away!

247
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,800
She didn't do anything wrong!

248
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:44,700
That's what you deserve!

249
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:48,200
Justice is served!

250
00:13:48,767 --> 00:13:49,900
Mom!

251
00:13:49,967 --> 00:13:52,367
Mom, stay with me!

252
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:54,300
Mom, don't leave me!

253
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,900
She didn't do anything wrong!

254
00:13:57,967 --> 00:14:02,333
Mom, don't leave me!

255
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:13,733
You come here almost every day.

256
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,100
This isn't right anymore.

257
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:18,133
You have to think
of your own life too.

258
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:21,167
And you're dragging
your aunt here with you.

259
00:14:22,267 --> 00:14:24,200
Mom...

260
00:14:24,267 --> 00:14:25,700
why did this happen?

261
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,733
I told them the truth.

262
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:31,033
Why didn't they listen to us?

263
00:14:32,433 --> 00:14:34,800
Because when you're poor...

264
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:38,900
you have no rights.

265
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:41,933
That's why I want you
to go to college.

266
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,500
So you'll have a better life.

267
00:14:45,667 --> 00:14:48,733
That's the only way
they'll listen to you.

268
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:51,200
You don't deserve
to be here, Mom.

269
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:53,100
We can't do anything about it.

270
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,667
It already happened.

271
00:14:55,733 --> 00:14:58,033
We don't have a choice
but to accept it.

272
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:07,600
But I can't let you waste
your life worrying about me.

273
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:08,533
No!
No, Mom.

274
00:15:09,567 --> 00:15:12,333
I'll come to visit you
on the weekends.

275
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,833
I promise.

276
00:15:15,167 --> 00:15:17,233
You can't visit me anymore.

277
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:18,733
Why not?

278
00:15:22,733 --> 00:15:28,300
Your mom and I
have made a decision, Eden.

279
00:15:28,367 --> 00:15:31,900
We will move
to the countryside for now.

280
00:15:31,967 --> 00:15:36,033
I found a job there and the cost
of living is cheaper there.

281
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:40,200
Your aunt will still be able
to send you to school.

282
00:15:40,267 --> 00:15:41,133
Mom!

283
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:43,700
I don't want to!

284
00:15:43,767 --> 00:15:45,867
Eden, listen to me.

285
00:15:46,967 --> 00:15:48,567
Your future is more important.

286
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:51,600
My life is ruined now.

287
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:56,667
I won't let your life
fall apart, too.

288
00:15:57,867 --> 00:16:01,533
But Mom, I don't want
to be away from you.

289
00:16:03,167 --> 00:16:05,233
Eden, I love you so much.

290
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,533
I love you so much too.

291
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,467
I love you so much.

292
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:14,033
Go on. You should go.

293
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:15,267
Yes, Amanda.

294
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:16,833
- Mom!
- We'll go.

295
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:18,300
Go on. Leave.

296
00:16:18,367 --> 00:16:18,833
Mom!

297
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:20,767
Eden, come here!

298
00:16:20,833 --> 00:16:21,933
- Mom!
- Eden!

299
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,933
Don't do this to me!

300
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,300
- Don't make me go.
- No.

301
00:16:25,367 --> 00:16:27,600
- Mom! I don't want to go!
- Yenyen, come on!

302
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:29,300
Mom, no!

303
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:30,967
Mom, I don't want to go!

304
00:16:31,033 --> 00:16:32,567
Don't be stubborn!

305
00:16:32,633 --> 00:16:33,400
Eden.
Go on.

306
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,733
Go home.

307
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,767
I'll take care of her.

308
00:16:37,833 --> 00:16:39,067
Come on, let's go.

309
00:16:39,133 --> 00:16:40,333
- Let's go home.
- Auntie, no!

310
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:40,833
Come on, Eden.

311
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:41,967
Let's go home.

312
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:43,067
Mom!

313
00:16:45,133 --> 00:16:47,867
I want to stay here.

314
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:49,100
Eden!

315
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:51,367
Mom!

316
00:16:51,433 --> 00:16:53,167
I don't want to go!

317
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:54,167
What are you doing?

318
00:16:54,233 --> 00:16:58,300
Are you not going to listen
to me?

319
00:16:58,367 --> 00:17:00,967
You have to be strong!

320
00:17:01,033 --> 00:17:04,133
Nothing will happen to you
if you stay with me!

321
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,367
Do you understand?

322
00:17:06,867 --> 00:17:08,567
Think about yourself.

323
00:17:08,633 --> 00:17:10,200
Your future!

324
00:17:11,967 --> 00:17:13,333
Go on.

325
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,500
Auntie, I don't want to go!

326
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:16,433
- Mom!
- Eden, come on!

327
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:17,467
Let's go home.

328
00:17:17,533 --> 00:17:18,033
Come on.

329
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:19,300
We have to go home.

330
00:17:19,367 --> 00:17:20,200
I don't want to!

331
00:17:20,267 --> 00:17:21,833
Come on, let's go home!
Let's go.

332
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:22,533
Let's go.

333
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:24,200
- Mom!
- Let's go home!

334
00:17:24,267 --> 00:17:25,633
Let's go home!

335
00:17:53,867 --> 00:17:55,167
Dear Mom...

336
00:17:56,033 --> 00:18:00,700
Aunt Dindi and I are doing
fine here in the province.

337
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:02,333
How are you doing?

338
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:05,867
I always think about you, Mom.

339
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:13,533
And I remember all your advice.

340
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:17,500
I always think about my future
whenever I'm in a competition,

341
00:18:17,567 --> 00:18:20,300
just like you always say.

342
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:29,300
Even though
you're not by my side,

343
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:32,933
I dedicate all my achievements
to you, my beloved mother.

344
00:19:51,767 --> 00:19:52,567
Mom!

345
00:19:52,633 --> 00:19:54,867
I didn't know you
were coming here.

346
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:57,067
I wanted to surprise you.

347
00:19:57,133 --> 00:19:59,867
Because I have good news.

348
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:04,200
From now on, Aunt Dindi and I
are staying here in Manila.

349
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:05,600
How come?

350
00:20:06,967 --> 00:20:10,100
Your daughter
is a swimmer, remember?

351
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:12,933
I got a scholarship.

352
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:17,667
So I'm going to continue
my studies here.

353
00:20:17,733 --> 00:20:22,133
Aunt Dindi got herself
a decent job here.

354
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,900
So we're closer to you.

355
00:20:25,967 --> 00:20:27,467
Eden...

356
00:20:27,533 --> 00:20:28,633
One more thing.

357
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:31,133
I talked to your lawyer.

358
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:34,733
I asked him about our appeal.

359
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:39,433
He said there's
a good chance of acquittal.

360
00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:45,200
It's been years since
we made an appeal.

361
00:20:45,267 --> 00:20:47,567
I'm losing hope.

362
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:49,600
Mom, don't talk like that.

363
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:56,033
We can't lose hope
in fighting for the truth.

364
00:20:56,100 --> 00:21:00,300
Mom, you'll get out
of here someday.

365
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:04,567
And we will be together again.

366
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:08,533
I missed you.

367
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:10,033
I missed you more.

368
00:21:12,933 --> 00:21:13,900
OMG, Eden!

369
00:21:13,967 --> 00:21:17,867
Tracy's inviting us to go
to her Uncle's bar.

370
00:21:17,933 --> 00:21:18,567
We're coming.

371
00:21:18,633 --> 00:21:19,867
I'll count you in, okay?

372
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:21,967
Wait, I can't go.

373
00:21:22,033 --> 00:21:23,600
Why not?

374
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:25,800
I have work, remember?

375
00:21:25,867 --> 00:21:27,333
But it's on Saturday!

376
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,333
You only work part-time, right?

377
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,367
One of the servers can't go
to work tomorrow.

378
00:21:31,433 --> 00:21:32,633
So I'll stand in for her.

379
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:34,867
I can't pass up
that extra income.

380
00:21:34,933 --> 00:21:38,567
I'll use the money for our
sports camp in Davao.

381
00:21:38,633 --> 00:21:41,100
Eden, whenever you're not busy
at school, you have work.

382
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:43,600
When you're off work,
you have to do sports.

383
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:46,733
How are you going to get a
boyfriend if you don't mingle?

384
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:49,800
I don't have time
for a boyfriend, okay?

385
00:21:49,867 --> 00:21:53,000
And we shouldn't
look for a boyfriend.

386
00:21:53,067 --> 00:21:54,767
It will come.

387
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,000
Sorry.

388
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:24,367
What in the world?

389
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:27,233
It was an accident.

390
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:28,367
I didn't mean it to happen.

391
00:22:28,433 --> 00:22:30,000
If you want I'll just replace
your water bottle.

392
00:22:30,067 --> 00:22:31,667
No need. The goal is that way.

393
00:22:31,733 --> 00:22:33,800
How did the ball get here?

394
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:36,633
This is the sidewalk.

395
00:22:36,700 --> 00:22:37,200
Sorry.

396
00:22:37,267 --> 00:22:39,233
I apologize, okay?

397
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:40,733
Let's go, Raichu.

398
00:22:46,233 --> 00:22:46,800
Eden!

399
00:22:46,867 --> 00:22:48,300
What a panty-dropper!

400
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,200
He's so handsome!

401
00:22:50,267 --> 00:22:51,800
You're overdoing it.

402
00:22:51,867 --> 00:22:53,667
He's good-looking but arrogant.

403
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:55,633
Why are you so picky?

404
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,600
You want someone
handsome and humble?

405
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:59,867
You're asking for too much.

406
00:22:59,933 --> 00:23:02,833
I won't waste my time
on guys like him.

407
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:04,800
And I don't think
he'll notice us.

408
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:08,733
Liar!
Let's go.

409
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:41,000
Here's your food.

410
00:23:41,067 --> 00:23:42,100
Thank you.

411
00:23:42,167 --> 00:23:42,800
Here you go.

412
00:23:42,867 --> 00:23:44,433
Pork buns.

413
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:45,667
Enjoy your food.

414
00:23:57,133 --> 00:23:58,867
Ma'am Rina?

415
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:00,333
Good afternoon, Ma'am.

416
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,600
Wait a minute.

417
00:24:07,567 --> 00:24:08,967
I know you!

418
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:12,633
You are that kid!

419
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:19,033
You're that criminal's daughter.

420
00:24:21,133 --> 00:24:23,933
Please don't say that.

421
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,367
It's true!

422
00:24:26,333 --> 00:24:30,433
Or perhaps they don't know
your background.

423
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:34,033
May I have the manager, please?

424
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:34,833
Yes, Ma'am.

425
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:37,900
What kind of restaurant is this?

426
00:24:37,967 --> 00:24:45,167
Why do you hire a daughter
of a convicted criminal?

427
00:24:45,233 --> 00:24:47,167
Ma'am, I'm begging you.

428
00:24:47,233 --> 00:24:49,433
Oh, now you're begging me?

429
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:53,167
You have the nerve to file
an appeal to the court.

430
00:24:53,233 --> 00:24:57,967
Did you really think the
High Court would take your side?

431
00:24:58,033 --> 00:25:00,133
My mom has nothing
to do with the crime.

432
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,933
What are you talking about?

433
00:25:03,267 --> 00:25:08,267
She is as guilty as hell!

434
00:25:08,333 --> 00:25:10,200
That's not true.

435
00:25:10,267 --> 00:25:11,567
You accused her of the crime.

436
00:25:11,633 --> 00:25:12,933
That's why she's in jail.

437
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,300
How dare you say that!

438
00:25:15,367 --> 00:25:25,333
She will pay for it all her life
until she becomes miserable!

439
00:25:26,267 --> 00:25:29,200
I am not going to eat
at a restaurant

440
00:25:29,267 --> 00:25:35,267
being served by the daughter
of a convict!

441
00:25:52,967 --> 00:25:54,633
Today is my day off.

442
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:58,467
I don't care how long you've
been asking me for a day off.

443
00:25:58,533 --> 00:26:01,167
I said you can't take
the day off today!

444
00:26:01,233 --> 00:26:01,800
I will hurt you!
Mom!

445
00:26:02,667 --> 00:26:04,200
Mom, he took something!

446
00:26:04,267 --> 00:26:05,367
Mom!

447
00:26:05,433 --> 00:26:06,667
What did you take?

448
00:26:06,733 --> 00:26:08,767
- Stay out of it!
- Mom!

449
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:11,733
- Mom!
- Raul!

450
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:12,900
Mom!

451
00:26:13,967 --> 00:26:15,600
No!

452
00:26:21,367 --> 00:26:25,600
Whereof, the court finds
the accused, Amanda Sta. Maria,

453
00:26:25,667 --> 00:26:29,300
guilty beyond reasonable doubt
as accomplice to the crime

454
00:26:29,367 --> 00:26:31,200
of robbery with homicide

455
00:26:31,267 --> 00:26:35,867
as defined and penalized
under the revised...

456
00:26:35,933 --> 00:26:37,333
Mom!

457
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:47,367
She will pay for it all her life
until she becomes miserable!

458
00:27:01,233 --> 00:27:03,333
Yeah, dude. Let's chill.

459
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:05,000
I just have to do
something for Coach.

460
00:27:05,067 --> 00:27:06,500
I'll see you later.

461
00:27:06,567 --> 00:27:07,700
Yup, see you.

462
00:27:38,433 --> 00:27:41,933
Miss, it's not yet
the end of the world.

463
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,967
Just hang in there.

464
00:28:25,967 --> 00:28:28,033
How long are you
going to be in Davao?

465
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:30,233
Three days.

466
00:28:30,300 --> 00:28:34,600
Some of the athletes
will stay to go island hopping.

467
00:28:34,667 --> 00:28:38,833
But I'll go home
right after our sports camp.

468
00:28:38,900 --> 00:28:42,233
I hope the higher court
will have a decision

469
00:28:42,300 --> 00:28:46,467
about our appeal
when I get back.

470
00:28:46,533 --> 00:28:48,433
You still haven't given up.

471
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:53,267
Mom, I will never give up.

472
00:28:53,333 --> 00:28:55,500
We might have
a moment of weakness.

473
00:28:55,600 --> 00:29:00,067
We might fall down for a bit.

474
00:29:00,133 --> 00:29:04,400
But we will get up and fight.

475
00:29:05,533 --> 00:29:08,567
Like people always say,

476
00:29:08,633 --> 00:29:11,000
never give up!

477
00:29:11,067 --> 00:29:13,000
Never give up.

478
00:29:14,867 --> 00:29:16,767
Thank you.

479
00:29:16,833 --> 00:29:20,500
You're my rock.

480
00:29:20,567 --> 00:29:22,600
I love you so much, Mom.

481
00:29:24,167 --> 00:29:27,633
We will fight.

482
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:33,667
Just a little bit more,
and we will get justice.

483
00:29:33,767 --> 00:29:37,733
And when I come back,
everything will be okay.

484
00:29:37,800 --> 00:29:39,967
We will go back from
where we started.

485
00:30:02,267 --> 00:30:04,900
We're about to get
the result of our appeal.

486
00:30:04,967 --> 00:30:06,500
I'm going out of jail!

487
00:30:06,567 --> 00:30:08,400
This is such good news!

488
00:30:08,467 --> 00:30:11,233
Eden will be happy!

489
00:30:11,300 --> 00:30:16,833
I would have lost hope
if it wasn't for her.

490
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:20,167
I owe her a lot!

491
00:30:20,233 --> 00:30:21,000
Help!

492
00:30:21,067 --> 00:30:22,400
Help!

493
00:30:22,467 --> 00:30:25,133
How can they release Amanda?

494
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,133
Come on!

495
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:27,867
It's not fair!

496
00:30:27,933 --> 00:30:30,033
Your son is coming home
from Davao.

497
00:30:30,100 --> 00:30:32,700
Do you want him
to see you drunk?

498
00:30:32,767 --> 00:30:35,400
You have to fight, Yenyen!

499
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:37,833
I want to see my mom!

500
00:30:37,900 --> 00:30:39,667
Is there anyone out there?

501
00:30:39,733 --> 00:30:41,033
Help!

502
00:30:42,133 --> 00:30:43,067
Help!
Miss!

503
00:30:48,033 --> 00:30:49,067
Help!
